issue_body:
* read and parse a cache file only on first cache use;
* serialize and save to the cache file [atexit](https://docs.python.org/3/library/atexit.html);
* apply `@memoize` automatically;
* include "dependency" files full paths in a key, so we can have different cache entries for different `package.json` and etc;
* include arguments in the key.

Hello,

I was wondering if yang2dsdl can validate a leafref in one module referencing a leaf in a different module (not an augment).

First module is leafrefs.yang :+1: 

module leafrefs {
  yang-version  1;
  namespace "http://example.com/leafrefs";
  prefix "lr";
  organization "Example";
  contact
    "abc@example.com";
  description
    "Leafrefs";
  revision "2015-02-10" {
    description "Initial revision";
  }
  list l1 {
    key "name";
    leaf name {
      type string;
    }
  }
}

Second module is leafrefs2.yang : 

module leafrefs2 {
  yang-version  1;
  namespace "http://example.com/leafrefs2";
  prefix "l2";
  import leafrefs {
    prefix "l";
  }
  organization "Example";
  contact
    "abc@example.com";
  description
    "leafrefs2";
  revision "2015-02-10" {
    description "Initial revision";
  }
  list l2 {
    key "id";
    leaf id {
      type uint8;
    }
    leaf l1-ref {
      type leafref {
        path "/l:l1/l:name";
        require-instance true;
      }
    }
  }
}

Data to be verified:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<data xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:netconf:base:1.0">
  <l1 xmlns="http://example.com/leafrefs">
    <name>local</name>
  </l1>
  <l2 xmlns="http://example.com/leafrefs2">
    <id>1</id>
    <l1-ref>abc</l1-ref>
  </l2>
</data>


Thanks,
Helen

I want to create a program for iOS that uses Dlib's face detector. I have compiled Dllib using cmake and have followed instructions from both Dlib's documentation and following an [article](http://prabhu.xyz/2017/05/29/getting-started-with-dlib-on-ios.html). 

At first I used Apple's own face detector and only shape predictor 68 face landmarks from Dlib library. At this point the library seemed to have compiled successfully. I wasn't getting any errors and everything was working fine. Then I decided I wanted to use Dlib's frontal face detector. It was when using this and calling get_frontal_face_detector() that the build failed and I started getting the Apple Mach-O Linker error saying Undefined symbols for architecture arm64:

